      • getLevelCollision

        public Construct getLevelCollision(Construct otherConstruct,
                                   Point finalPosition)
        Checks if a specified Construct has collided with another Construct in the level of type Terrain. If the Construct does not collide with any elements of the terrain the function will return null. Otherwise the function will return the first element in the terrain that the specified Construct collides with.
        Parameters:
        otherConstruct - A Construct that may collide with an element of the terrain.
        finalPosition - The Point that denotes the final position that Construct will have.
        Returns:
        The first element from the terrain that the specified specified Construct collided with, if any.
        See Also:
        Construct, Terrain, Point

      • checkForEnemyCollision

        public Construct checkForEnemyCollision(Construct otherConstruct,
                                        Point finalPosition)
        Checks if a specified Construct has collided with another Construct in the level of type Enemy. If the Construct does not collide with any of the enemies in the level the function will return null. Otherwise the function will return the first enemy in the level that the specified Construct collides with.
        Parameters:
        otherConstruct - A Construct that may collide with a Enemy in the level.
        finalPosition - The Point that denotes the final position that Construct will have.
        Returns:
        The first element from the set of enemies in the level that the specified specified Construct collided with, if any.
        See Also:
        Construct, Enemy, Point

      • checkForObjectiveCollision

        public Construct checkForObjectiveCollision(Construct otherConstruct,
                                            Point finalPosition)
        Checks if a specified Construct has collided with another Construct in the Level of type Objective. If the Construct does not collide with any of the objectives in the level the function will return null. Otherwise the function will return the first enemy in the level that the specified Construct collides with.
        Parameters:
        otherConstruct - A Construct that may collide with a Enemy in the level.
        finalPosition - The Point that denotes the final position that Construct will have.
        Returns:
        The first element from the set of enemies in the level that the specified specified Construct collided with, if any.
        See Also:
        Construct, Objective, Point
